  "response": "The average amount of human excreta produced by a person can vary based on diet, health, and lifestyle. However, on general terms:\n\n1. **Urine**: An average adult typically produces about 800 to 2,000 milliliters (ml) of urine per day.\n2. **Feces**: An average adult produces about 100 to 250 grams of feces per day.\n\nThese figures can vary widely, but they provide a general estimate of typical excreta production. Factors such as hydration levels, dietary habits, and physical activity all play a role in individual variation.",
